<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: Cannot enable Raspi 3 integrated bluetooth</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>Speedytaco wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>I cannot for the life of me get the raspi 3 Bluetooth to work. Bluetooth status shows that it is &quot;inactive (dead).<br/>I have installed bluez and Bluetooth and yes I&#039;ve started Bluetooth but nothing will work for me. Please help.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Try</p><div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>sudo apt-get install pi-bluetooth</p></div></blockquote></div><p>To see the status:</p><div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>systemctl status bluetooth</p></div></blockquote></div><p>To start bluetooth:</p><div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>systemctl start bluetooth</p></div></blockquote></div>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>Andre &quot;qr0f1l3R&quot; P. - Parrot Ambassador - Founder of the German community</p><p>GPG Fingerprint: 290A C689 2EB1 45F6 5E74 2C11 99B1 2DF0 E85A E4E6<br/>GPG Info: <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vindex&amp;fingerprint=on&amp;search=0x99B12DF0E85AE4E6" rel="nofollow">http://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vindex … F0E85AE4E6</a><br/>GPG Key: <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=get&amp;search=0x99B12DF0E85AE4E6" rel="nofollow">http://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=get&amp;se … F0E85AE4E6</a></p></div>
